==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Postfix
<hw>Post"fix</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Postfixes</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Pref. <ets>post-</ets> +
<ets>-fix</ets>, as in <ets>prefix</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>postfixe</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Gram.)</fld> <def>A letter, syllable,
or word, added to the end of another word; a suffix.</def>
<rj><au>Parkhurst.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Postfix</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Postfix
<hw>Post*fix"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To annex;
specifically <fld>(Gram.)</fld>, to add or annex, as a letter, syllable,
or word, to the end of another or principal word; to suffix.</def>
<rj><au>Parkhurst.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Postfrontal</ent>⟦br⟧
